  "text": "• In the steady state phase, each CH creates a TDMA schedule by assigning time slots to its member nodes to avoid intra-cluster collisions. The member nodes send data to the CH according to its assigned time slot [CITATION_1] . The mobile collector then collects data from the CHs based on Ant-Colony Optimisation (ACO). Now, Fuzzy Logic can be appropriately used to model decision making behaviour where a lot of factors are involved. Furthermore, Particle Swarm Optimisation (PSO) can be used to tune the parameters of the fuzzy logic controllers for better performance of the network. The proposed algorithm uses fuzzy descriptors and PSO to form clusters in the network and the movement of the mobile collector is determined using ACO to mitigate the hot-spot problem in a wireless sensor network.",
